Gamma detector array DANCE, consisting of 160
BaF2 crystals which cover a solid angle of
approximately 3.5 Pi was used for gamma ray
detection. A single gamma-ray efficiency was 85%.

Spallation neutrons were produced by a pulsed
800 MeV proton beam with a repetition rate of 20 Hz
impinging on a pair of tungsten targets. Neutrons are
reflected by the moderator and travel down a 20.2-m
flight path to the target location.
